    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-08-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="432"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d432">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Dupuy de Lôme</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-08-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 31, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Attorney-General and the naval and revenue authorities will be advised of
                    your statement in to-day’s telegram that filibustering expeditions are in
                    progress at New Orleans. Details should be furnished. Your consul there should
                    communicate all information he has directly to United States attorney, and, if
                    the facts suffice, make complaint under oath upon which judicial steps may be
                    regularly taken, and the other executive branches may act.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
